Living To 101(Horizon) 2008 02 19 avi

Dr Brian Wilcox investigates why particular groups of people exhibit extraordinary longevity. Travelling to Japan, Sardinia and California, he tests the roles of diet, genes and religious faith, the three factors believed among the most important in reaching advanced old age, wondering if any of these could be harnessed to provide the elixir of life
